        "created_at": "2019-02-21T01:20:49.812Z",
        "cooked": "<p><a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/blob-java.html\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Here</a> is the page describing storage of blobs in Java. You can see the two lines for determining the chunk size below:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">int numChunks = (data.length() + CHUNK_SIZE - 1)/CHUNK_SIZE;\nint chunkSize = (data.length() + numChunks)/numChunks;\n</code></pre>\n<p>What is the purpose of the <code>chunkSize</code> variable. Why not simple use the <code>CHUNK_SIZE</code> constant?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 3,
        "updated_at": "2019-02-21T01:20:49.812Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
