        "id": 3487,
        "name": "Christophe Chevalier",
        "username": "KrzysFR",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/krzysfr/{size}/43_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-02-21T21:39:30.729Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I think it\u2019s trying to equalize the size of all chunks. Using CHUNK_SIZE, the last chunk may be smaller than the other ones while here they all have the same size\u2026 though I\u2019m not sure if this is a real concern: I don\u2019t see any perf reason to go one way or the other, but equalizing the size of all chunks makes it a bit difficult to support <em>append</em> semantics on your blobs.</p>\n<p>Another thing: the code referenced use the Tuple encoding to encode the <em>value</em> \u2026 which is a bit wasteful. I would have simply truncated the bytes obtained from the UTF-8 representation of the string into smaller chunks. This is even simpler when storing plain bytes.</p>",
        "post_number": 2,
        "post_type": 1,
