        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/krzysfr/{size}/43_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-02-21T21:47:26.282Z",
        "cooked": "<p>If you are looking for a \u201cfull featured\u201d blob layer implementation, there was an original Blob Layer sample written in python, but it is probably not available anymore.</p>\n<p>I did port it to C# a long time ago, it\u2019s still available here: <a href=\"https://github.com/Doxense/foundationdb-dotnet-client/blob/master/FoundationDB.Layers.Common/Blobs/FdbBlob.cs\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">https://github.com/Doxense/foundationdb-dotnet-client/blob/master/FoundationDB.Layers.Common/Blobs/FdbBlob.cs</a></p>\n<p>Disclaimer: In practice, I never used this implementation because I don\u2019t really need to support sparse files or shrink/truncate blobs and the representation of the keys is a bit weird. The implementation we use is a lot more straight-forward, and adds support for compression, deduplication and attribute indexing.</p>",
